        "@value": "Laura Taler brings us on a site-specific cinematic journey through the NAC&rsquo;s theatrical underworld where the art of crafting private dreams is made public. While conjuring a ninety-nine-year-old photo of Bronislava Nijinska, Taler poses a series of questions about performance, the fallibility and concreteness of language, and the practice of turning the&nbsp;self inside&nbsp;out.&nbsp; &nbsp;"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/url": [
      {
        "@value": "https://nac-cna.ca/en/event/40241"
      }
    ],
    "http://schema.org/image": [
